  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious financial crime with a comprehensive legal framework designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute such activities. Here's an overview of the key aspects:\n\n1. International Legal Framework\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) Recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. Domestic Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act (United States)\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (United Kingdom)\n- Similar national legislative frameworks globally\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Customer Due Diligence (CDD)\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Suspicious Transaction Reporting\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- Transaction monitoring\n\n4. Regulatory Compliance\n- Financial institutions must implement robust AML programs\n- Regular reporting to financial intelligence units\n- Risk-based approach to detecting potential money laundering\n\n5. Criminal Penalties\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\n6. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing between jurisdictions\n- Extradition agreements\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n\nThis framework aims to prevent financial crimes and track illicit financial flows.",
